data.title: FRANC Definition & Meaning
data.meta_description: Franc definition: an aluminum or nickel coin and monetary unit of France, Belgium, and Luxembourg until the euro  was adopted, equal to 100 centimes. Abbreviations. See examples of FRANC used in a sentence.
